import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['route'] = data['origin'] + ' to ' + data['destination']
    route_counts = data['route'].value_counts().reset_index()
    route_counts.columns = ['route', 'count']
    top_routes = route_counts.head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='route', y='count', data=top_routes, palette='Blues_d')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Route')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    for i, v in enumerate(top_routes['count']):
        ax.text(i, v + 50, str(v), ha='center')
    plt.title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='count', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
